com.orchestranetworks.schema.info
Interface SchemaFacetTableRef

All Superinterfaces:
SchemaFacet, SchemaFacetEnumeration
public interface SchemaFacetTableRef
extends SchemaFacetEnumeration

This interface represents the foreign key constraint associated with a node (osd:tableRef).

Dependencies and Validation

For optimizing the validation process of this foreign key constraint, dependencies are automatically inferred from its definition.

The following explicit dependencies are automatically defined:

  1. Dependency on insertion and deletion on the target table specified by this foreign key constraint. This dependency is of the following types:
    • either DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToInsertAndDelete(SchemaNode) in the default case;
    • or DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToInsertAndDeleteInOtherInstance(Path, AdaptationReference), if this foreign key constraint defines a data set container;
    • or DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToInsertAndDeleteInOtherInstance(Path, AdaptationReference, HomeKey), if this foreign key constraint defines a data set container in another data space.

  2. Dependencies on insertion, deletion and modification to criterion nodes if this foreign key constraint defines an XPath filter. For example if this constraint defines the XPath filter author_id = ${../author_id}, then a dependency to the left node author_id will be defined. This dependency is of the following types:

    • either DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToInsertDeleteAndModify(SchemaNode), in the default case;
    • or DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToInsertDeleteAndModifyInOtherInstance(SchemaNode, AdaptationReference), if this foreign key constraint defines an data set container;
    • or DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToInsertDeleteAndModifyInOtherInstance(SchemaNode, AdaptationReference, HomeKey), if this foreign key constraint defines an data set container in another data space.
    Where the argument SchemaNode is ${../author_id}.

    Dependencies on modification to the right part ${../author_id} will also be defined. In this case, the dependency is the same as: DependenciesDefinitionContext.addDependencyToModify(SchemaNode) where the argument SchemaNode is ${../author_id}.

This implies that the validation result of this foreign key constraint depends only on updates of the target table that have been specified by these explicit dependencies. Except for the change of the local value, the validation result will not be affected by any other external event.

However, the dependencies of this foreign key constraint are set to Unknown if this foreign key constraint defines:

  • a programmatic filter with no explicit dependencies.
  • an XPath filter specifying criterion nodes that are not in the target table.

IMPORTANT NOTES:

  • The dependencies automatically defined in this constraint will be used in addition to those optionally defined by a filter.
  • In user interface mode (EBX5), this foreign key constraint is always called when user input is submitted.

See Also:
foreign key constraint, validation, SchemaNode.getFacetOnTableReference(), TableRefFilterContext
